         Mana burn only does that kind of damage if the wizard gets a critical hit.  If it was a normal blast that didn't crit that 15k nuke would be 7500.  Now compare that to a necro that has 4000hp with raid buffs (not all that hard to obtain).  The necro will do 4000 dmg plus the 1500 pt dot.  That's 5500 damage plus we are not out of the fight after that, Lifeburn uses no mana. </P><P>The only unfair thing between the two is theirs can crit and ours can't.  Hopefully someday this will be address but even without critical hits Lifeburn is a great addition to our damage output.  It's added damage for us, while a wizard using manaburn would do far less damage than they normally could in a fight.</P><P><BR>&lt;P&gt;<center>&lt;IMG BORDER=0 SRC="http://seadan.netfirms.com/tome2.jpg"&gt;</center><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
