        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I think the basic balancing act on this is that wizards can either use their mana to manaburn, or to use their regular nukes. They do 15k with manaburn, they do 25k with spells. One is instant, and that 15k is only on crits. One takes a long long time, and its easy to overagro and die.</P><P>Whats up with us? We land DoT's, nukes, finally run out of mana, and we can still toss in that extra 4k. </P><P>What do we still need? DoT Crits, a chance for our DoT's to do double damage. This should effect our lifeburn and all our other DoT's. Affliction Fury!</P><P>Warlock<BR>Shadow Council<BR>Terris-Thule<BR><a href="http://www.shadowcouncil.com" target="_blank">http://www.shadowcouncil.com</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6164" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6164</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
