		<a name="37448"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/08/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 18:48:01</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=6459"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=6459')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=37448&amp;TOPIC_ID=4749&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Lifeburn+VS+manaburn&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Greetings Dark Ones!</P><P>58 Wizard here. Just wanted to comment that, from a Wizard perspective, we NEED to have something that is a class defining role, which both Verant and the EQ players have come to expect to be damage (I dont really care for this perception, but thats how the game is).</P><P>The thing is, wizards have about 2 things, nukes and ports. Ports dont do alot for us in terms of combat (except to get to the fight relatively quickly), so it would seem nukes are the BIGGEST class defining ability we have. I would humbly submit that to let necros, or any other class, to be able to have the same POTENTIAL amount of "fast" damage that a wizard can do would simply take away the one thing that is supposed to define us. Again, I dont really care the idea that wizards are "nukers" plain and simple, since they are not portrayed that way in most fantasy RPG settings, but that is the way EQ made them.</P><P>Manaburn is simply an extension of that thinking. It was pointed out that UNLESS a wizard gets a critical on a manaburn it will do somewhere around 7500 dmg. Without the crits, manaburn is not that far ahead of the necro ability to lifeburn. IF it was made so that lifeburn could crit, necros would then be in the same league as wizards in terms of dmg output, which I think would take away from our class defining role of "masters of dmg."</P><P>---Gandalf the Wizard</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

