         Just to clarify a few things.</P><P>a) It's dd + the dot. Now I don't know how the dot part works entirely, but I should test it in a duel I guess. I've done 4800dd then got the dot.</P><P>b) It's not always instant aggro / summon. There are tons of mobs, mostly rooted ones it seems that you can burn and they won't summon you at all. Some good tips are to have a skin spell up and maybe a vm before you do it, along with fd / hs / qvx right after.</P><P>c) Wizards actually have to spend 18 points to get mana burn.</P><P>d) Wizards are dd kings, they should have a much better burn then us, and while I'd like to have the ability to crit, I don't think it's really that big of a deal. We have to raise hp for a better burn, they have to raise mana.</P><P>Crit dots are a great idea, but instead we just need some better dots and of course dot stacking.</P><P>Zaar Deth'Mortis<BR>Leader of Triton<BR><a href="http://www.tritonguild.com" target="_blank">http://www.tritonguild.com</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43499" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43499</a><BR>"Please go back to your fantasy playstyle and leave the real necromancers alone." - Potus<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
